Problem: Climbing Stairs
Topic: Dynamic Programming
Difficulty: Easy

Approach:
Use iterative dynamic programming (Fibonacci pattern). Each step count is the sum of ways to reach the previous two steps.

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(1)

Code:
class Solution {
public:
    int climbStairs(int n) {
        if(n<=2)   return n;
        int curr;
        int s1=1;
        int s2=2;
        for(int i=3;i<=n;i++){
            curr=s1+s2;
            s1=s2;
            s2=curr;
        }
        return s2;
    }
};
